label: uncl3155
comment: Code specifying the type of communication address.

values.label: Circuit switching
values.comment: A process that, on demand, connects two or more data terminal equipments and permits the exclusive use of a data circuit between them until the connection is released (ISO).

values.label: SITA
values.comment: Communications number assigned by Societe Internationale de Telecommunications Aeronautiques (SITA).

values.label: ARINC
values.comment: Communications number assigned by Aeronautical Radio Inc.

values.label: AT&T mailbox
values.comment: AT&T mailbox identifier.

values.label: Peripheral device
values.comment: Peripheral device identification.

values.label: U.S. Defense Switched Network
values.comment: The switched telecommunications network of the United States Department of Defense.

values.label: U.S. federal telecommunications system
values.comment: The switched telecommunications network of the United States government.

values.label: World Wide Web
values.comment: Data exchange via the World Wide Web.

values.label: International calling country code
values.comment: Identifies that portion of an international telephone number representing the country code to be used when calling internationally.

values.label: Alternate telephone
values.comment: Identifies the alternate telephone number.

values.label: Videotex number
values.comment: Code that identifies the communications number for the online videotex service.

values.label: Cellular phone
values.comment: Identifies the cellular phone number.

values.label: International telephone direct line
values.comment: The international telephone direct line number.

values.label: O.F.T.P. (ODETTE File Transfer Protocol)
values.comment: ODETTE File Transfer Protocol.

values.label: Uniform Resource Location (URL)
values.comment: Identification of the Uniform Resource Location (URL) Synonym: World wide web address.

values.label: Very High Frequency (VHF) radio telephone
values.comment: VHF radio telephone.

values.label: X.400 address for mail text
values.comment: The X.400 address accepting information in the body text of a message.

values.label: AS1 address
values.comment: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS1 protocol for MIME based EDI .

values.label: AS2 address
values.comment: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS2 protocol.

values.label: AS3 address
values.comment: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS3 protocol.

values.label: File Transfer Protocol
values.comment: Address capable for receiving message in accordance with the File Transfer Protocol (IETF RFC 959 et. al.).

values.label: Inmarsat call number
values.comment: Contact number based on Inmarsat.

values.label: Radio communication call sign
values.comment: Contact number for radio communication based on call sign.

values.label: Cable address
values.comment: The communication number identifies a cable address.

values.label: EDI transmission
values.comment: Number identifying the service and service user.

values.label: Electronic mail
values.comment: Exchange of mail by electronic means.

values.label: Extension
values.comment: Telephone extension.

values.label: File transfer access method
values.comment: According to ISO.

values.label: Telefax
values.comment: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media.

values.label: GEIS (General Electric Information Service) mailbox
values.comment: The communication number identifies a GEIS mailbox.

values.label: IBM information exchange
values.comment: The communication number identifies an IBM IE mailbox.

values.label: Internal mail
values.comment: Internal mail address/number.

values.label: Mail
values.comment: Postal service document delivery.

values.label: Postbox number
values.comment: The communication number identifies a postbox.

values.label: Packet switching
values.comment: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

values.label: S.W.I.F.T.
values.comment: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

values.label: Telephone
values.comment: Voice/data transmission by telephone.

values.label: Telegraph
values.comment: Text transmission via telegraph.

values.label: Telex
values.comment: Transmission of text/data via telex.

values.label: Telemail
values.comment: Transmission of text/data via telemail.

values.label: Teletext
values.comment: Transmission of text/data via teletext.

values.label: TWX
values.comment: Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

values.label: X.400 address
values.comment: The X.400 address.

values.label: Pager
values.comment: Identifies that the communication number is for a pager.

values.label: International telephone switchboard
values.comment: The international telephone switchboard number.

values.label: National telephone direct line
values.comment: The national telephone direct line number.

values.label: National telephone switchboard
values.comment: The national telephone switchboard number.
